author: Mark Judge

description: EXCLUSIVE — Dr. Marc Siegel was motivated by his centenarian parents to pen his book about medical miracles, The Miracles Among Us: How God’s Grace Plays a Role in Healing. “I noticed that they navigated near misses over time that were oftentimes guided by amazing medicine or coincidence or faith,” Siegel told The Washington Examiner. author: Kate Monroe
description: Every Veterans Day, Americans say, “Thank you for your service.” But, while it may be heartfelt, it’s not enough. If you really want to honor veterans, don’t say “thank you” — ask, “How can I help?” Each year, roughly 200,000 service members transition out of the military and back into civilian life, only to find themselves in the […]
title: Veterans defended our homeland and now they need a place in it

author: Washington Examiner Staff
description: Numerous people gathered for hours at the University of California, Berkeley, on Monday to protest a Turning Point USA event scheduled for that night. author: Washington Examiner Staff

author: Ramsey Touchberry
description: The longest government shutdown in U.S. history is one step closer to coming to an end, after the Senate passed short-term funding Monday on the 41st day of the shutdown. The measure, which passed 60-40 with bipartisan support, required a simple majority and now heads to the House for final passage, where it is expected […]
